title: Domestic economy fares up 10pc as Qantas, Virgin maintain truce
text:
Domestic economy fares up 10pc as Qan... Domestic economy fares up 10pc as Qantas, Virgin maintain truce Next Story Prev Story 46 min ago Read more: The Age 
Travellers are continuing to cop increases in fares for domestic flights as Qantas and Virgin Australia maintain their truce after their so-called "capacity war". On flights within Australia, economy fares rose more than 10 per cent in the three months to June, compared with the same period a year earlier, and a detailed analysis by Deutsche Bank has highlighted further price increases into the first quarter of the new financial year.   The Age.
